# byronwade/ui ‚Äî code conventions

These are the **structural/style** rules for editing this repo's registry source. They sit on top
of the *content* Design DNA (tokens, typography, Base UI + CVA) in `AGENTS.md` and the shipped rule
`registry/rules/byronwade-ui.mdc`. Full prose: `docs/CONVENTIONS.md`. Treat these as constraints.

**Design engineer principles** (`AGENTS.md`) ‚Äî usefulness, whole-experience ownership, constraints,
inclusion, excellence, team improvement ‚Äî apply alongside these conventions.

## Where things go

- UI primitive ‚Üí `registry/ui/<slug>.tsx`
- Composite / pattern ‚Üí `registry/components/<slug>.tsx`
- Shared helper / hook ‚Üí `registry/lib/<slug>.ts`
- Optional CVA split ‚Üí `registry/ui/<slug>-variants.ts`
- Example ‚Üí `content/examples/<slug>/default.tsx` ¬∑ Test ‚Üí `tests/components/<slug>.test.tsx`

One component family per file. Composites compose primitives ‚Äî never bespoke one-off elements.

## Naming

- Filenames are **kebab-case** and equal the registry slug.
- Components **PascalCase**; props type `<Component>Props`; variants `<component>Variants`.
- `data-slot` values kebab-case, namespaced by component (`button`, `button-spinner`).

## Exports

- **Named exports at the file bottom**: `export { Button, buttonVariants }` then `export type { ‚Ä¶ }`.
- **No `export default`** for components.

## Imports

- Consumer paths only: `@/components/ui/‚Ä¶`, `@/components/‚Ä¶`, `@/lib/‚Ä¶`. **Never `../`.**

## Formatting

- Prettier, **`semi: false`** (no semicolons), double quotes, trailing commas. Run `npm run format`.

## Comments

- Minimal / self-documenting. Comment only non-obvious logic or tricky public API. No header
  boilerplate, no comments that restate the code ‚Äî a comment explains *why*, not *what*.

## Component shape

Build on `@base-ui/react`; variants in a `cva()` block; **`data-slot`** on every rendered part;
accept `className` and merge via **`cn()`** from `@/lib/utils`; tokens only for color; editorial
typography (no `font-bold` on display/section). Long-form copy uses **`reading-ui`** or
**`reading-prose`** ‚Äî not full-bleed `text-sm`. Ship a test (variants/states + `axe`) and an example.

Copy `registry/ui/button.tsx` (primitive) or `registry/components/status-pill.tsx` (composite).

## Enforcement

`npm run validate` (structural + registry gates, incl. `check:conventions`) and `npm run test:ci`
(tests + coverage) run in CI. Formatting: `npm run check:format`. On-system tokens: `npm run lint:on-system`.
